<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="63" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="63">
12. 
<taxonomicName LSID="3C8FF87F-8B1B-5939-B7DA-F1A9BF693A21" authority="(J. R. Sahlberg, 1913), stat. rest." authorityName=", stat. rest." baseAuthorityName="J. R. Sahlberg" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calomera aulicoides" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aulicoides">Calomera aulicoides (J.R. Sahlberg, 1913), stat. rest.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="63" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="63">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="63">On sandy and stony banks close to freshwater (the Jordan River, Sea of Galilee), especially in wadis. Also found in salty habitats close to the Dead Sea. Diurnal.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="63" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="63">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="63">
Throughout the year (records from February to December) (
<bibRefCitation author="Nussbaum, Y" journalOrPublisher="YES Quarterly" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" pagination="7 - 15" refId="B87" refString="Nussbaum, Y, 1987. Tiger beetles of Israel and Sinai (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). YES Quarterly 4: 7 - 15" title="Tiger beetles of Israel and Sinai (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." volume="4" year="1987">Nussbaum 1987</bibRefCitation>
, own observations).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="63" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="63">Distribution range.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="63">
From Egypt and southern Turkey to Iran (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.21426/B6110089" author="Cassola, F" journalOrPublisher="Biogeographia" pageId="39" pageNumber="82" pagination="229 - 276" refId="B29" refString="Cassola, F, 1999. Studies on tiger beetles. CVII. The cicindelid fauna of Anatolia: faunistics and biogeography (Coleoptera, Cicindelidae). Biogeographia 20: 229 - 276, DOI: https://doi.org/10.21426/B6110089" title="Studies on tiger beetles. CVII. The cicindelid fauna of Anatolia: faunistics and biogeography (Coleoptera, Cicindelidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.21426/B6110089" volume="20" year="1999">Cassola 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Korell, A" journalOrPublisher="Entomologia Basiliensia" pageId="42" pageNumber="85" pagination="93 - 111" refId="B72" refString="Korell, A, 1988. Die Cicindeliden (Coleoptera) Anatoliens. Entomologia Basiliensia 12: 93 - 111" title="Die Cicindeliden (Coleoptera) Anatoliens." volume="12" year="1988">Korell 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mandl, K" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Arbeiten aus dem Museum Frey" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" pagination="117 - 176" refId="B81" refString="Mandl, K, 1981b. Revision der unter Cicindela lunulata F. im Weltkatalog der Cicindelinae zusammengefassten Formen (Coleoptera, Cicindelidae). Entomologische Arbeiten aus dem Museum Frey 29: 117 - 176" title="Revision der unter Cicindela lunulata F. im Weltkatalog der Cicindelinae zusammengefassten Formen (Coleoptera, Cicindelidae)." volume="29" year="1981 b">Mandl 1981b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="64" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="63">Distribution in the southern Levant.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="64" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">
In Israel and Jordan along the Jordan Valley from the Hula Valley and the Sea of Galilee to the Dead Sea region, and in the Arava 
<pageBreakToken pageId="21" pageNumber="64" start="start">Valley</pageBreakToken>
. In Sinai on the Mediterranean Coast and in South Sinai (
<bibRefCitation author="Abdel-Dayem, MS" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Entomological Society of Egypt" pageId="38" pageNumber="81" pagination="193 - 217" refId="B1" refString="Abdel-Dayem, MS, El-Haewagri, MSA, Yassan, SA, 2003. A review of the Egyptian species of tiger beetles (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Cicindelidae). Bulletin of the Entomological Society of Egypt 80: 193 - 217" title="A review of the Egyptian species of tiger beetles (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Cicindelidae)." volume="80" year="2003">Abdel-Dayem et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.578.7383" author="Matalin, AV" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" pagination="115 - 160" refId="B82" refString="Matalin, AV, Chikatunov, VI, 2016. The tiger beetles (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Cicindelinae) of Israel and adjacent lands. ZooKeys 578: 115 - 160, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.578.7383" title="The tiger beetles (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Cicindelinae) of Israel and adjacent lands." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.578.7383" volume="578" year="2016">Matalin and Chikatunov 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nussbaum, Y" journalOrPublisher="YES Quarterly" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" pagination="7 - 15" refId="B87" refString="Nussbaum, Y, 1987. Tiger beetles of Israel and Sinai (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). YES Quarterly 4: 7 - 15" title="Tiger beetles of Israel and Sinai (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." volume="4" year="1987">Nussbaum 1987</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="65" pageId="21" pageNumber="64" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="64">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="64">
In the past most authors ranked this taxon as a subspecies (or even as a form with a rank below the subspecies) of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1787" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calomera littoralis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="littoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="64">Calomera littoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(or of another taxon of this species group) (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mandl, K" journalOrPublisher="Arbeiten ueber morphologische und taxonomische Entomologie aus Berlin-Dahlem" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" pagination="239 - 246" refId="B78" refString="Mandl, K, 1934. Cicindela lunulata Fabr. und ihre Rassen. Arbeiten ueber morphologische und taxonomische Entomologie aus Berlin-Dahlem 1: 239 - 246" title="Cicindela lunulata Fabr. und ihre Rassen." volume="1" year="1934">Mandl 1934</bibRefCitation>
). However, later 
<bibRefCitation author="Mandl, K" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Arbeiten aus dem Museum Frey" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" pagination="117 - 176" refId="B81" refString="Mandl, K, 1981b. Revision der unter Cicindela lunulata F. im Weltkatalog der Cicindelinae zusammengefassten Formen (Coleoptera, Cicindelidae). Entomologische Arbeiten aus dem Museum Frey 29: 117 - 176" title="Revision der unter Cicindela lunulata F. im Weltkatalog der Cicindelinae zusammengefassten Formen (Coleoptera, Cicindelidae)." volume="29" year="1981 b">Mandl (1981b)</bibRefCitation>
ranked 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName=", stat. rest." baseAuthorityName="J. R. Sahlberg" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calomera aulicoides" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aulicoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="64">Calomera aulicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a species, though only few authors accepted this ranking (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Korell, A" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="42" pageNumber="85" pagination="221 - 224" refId="B71" refString="Korell, A, 1984. Ueber Cephalota zarudniana und drei weitere Cicindelinae -Arten aus Syrien (Col.: Cicindelidae). Entomologische Zeitschrift 94: 221 - 224" title="Ueber Cephalota zarudniana und drei weitere Cicindelinae - Arten aus Syrien (Col.: Cicindelidae)." volume="94" year="1984">Korell 1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Werner, K" journalOrPublisher="Science Nat, Venette" pageId="44" pageNumber="87" refId="B109" refString="Werner, K, 1991. Cicindelidae 1. Science Nat, Venette" title="Cicindelidae 1." year="1991">Werner 1991</bibRefCitation>
), and the majority rank it as a subspecies (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.21426/B6110089" author="Cassola, F" journalOrPublisher="Biogeographia" pageId="39" pageNumber="82" pagination="229 - 276" refId="B29" refString="Cassola, F, 1999. Studies on tiger beetles. CVII. The cicindelid fauna of Anatolia: faunistics and biogeography (Coleoptera, Cicindelidae). Biogeographia 20: 229 - 276, DOI: https://doi.org/10.21426/B6110089" title="Studies on tiger beetles. CVII. The cicindelid fauna of Anatolia: faunistics and biogeography (Coleoptera, Cicindelidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.21426/B6110089" volume="20" year="1999">Cassola 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.578.7383" author="Matalin, AV" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" pagination="115 - 160" refId="B82" refString="Matalin, AV, Chikatunov, VI, 2016. The tiger beetles (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Cicindelinae) of Israel and adjacent lands. ZooKeys 578: 115 - 160, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.578.7383" title="The tiger beetles (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Cicindelinae) of Israel and adjacent lands." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.578.7383" volume="578" year="2016">Matalin and Chikatunov 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Putchkov, AV" editor="Loebl, I" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="44" pageNumber="87" pagination="99 - 118" refId="B94" refString="Putchkov, AV, Matalin, AV, 2003. Subfamily Cicindelinae. In: Loebl, I, Smetana, A, Eds., Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera Volume 1 Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga. Apollo Books, Stenstrup: 99 - 118" title="Subfamily Cicindelinae." volumeTitle="Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera Volume 1 Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga." year="2003">Putchkov and Matalin 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Putchkov, AV" editor="Loebl, I" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="44" pageNumber="87" pagination="217 - 249" refId="B95" refString="Putchkov, AV, Matalin, AV, 2017. Subfamily Cicindelinae. In: Loebl, I, Loebl, D, Eds., Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera Volume 1 Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga. Apollo Books, Stenstrup: 217 - 249" title="Subfamily Cicindelinae." volumeTitle="Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera Volume 1 Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga." year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wiesner, J" journalOrPublisher="Erna Bauer, Keltern" pageId="45" pageNumber="88" refId="B114" refString="Wiesner, J, 1992. Checklist of the tiger beetles of the world. Erna Bauer, Keltern" title="Checklist of the tiger beetles of the world." year="1992">Wiesner 1992</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Pesarini, C" journalOrPublisher="Cornell University Press, Ithaca and London" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" refId="B92" refString="Pesarini, C, Monzini, V, 2010. Insetti della fauna Italiana - Coleotteri Carabidi I. Natura: Rivista di Scienze Naturali 100/2: 1-152." title="Insetti della fauna Italiana - Coleotteri Carabidi I. Natura: Rivista di Scienze Naturali 100 / 2: 1 - 152." year="2010">Pesarini and Monzini (2010</bibRefCitation>
: 10) are, to our knowledge, the only authors from the last years, who ranked 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName=", stat. rest." baseAuthorityName="J. R. Sahlberg" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calomera aulicoides" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aulicoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="64">Calomera aulicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species. However, the authors seem to have confused it with 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Baudi di Selve" baseAuthorityYear="1864" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calomera aphrodisia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aphrodisia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="64">Calomera aphrodisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Baudi, 1864), which occurs in Sicily (
<bibRefCitation author="Brandmayr, P" journalOrPublisher="Manuali e Linee Guida, Rome" pageId="39" pageNumber="82" refId="B25" refString="Brandmayr, P, Zetto, T, Pizzolotto, R, Casale, A, Vigna-Taglianti, A, 2005. I Coleotteri Carabidi per la valutazione ambientale e la conservazione della biodiversita. Agenzia per la protezione dell'ambiente per i servizi tecnici. Manuali e Linee Guida, Rome" title="I Coleotteri Carabidi per la valutazione ambientale e la conservazione della biodiversita. Agenzia per la protezione dell'ambiente per i servizi tecnici." year="2005">Brandmayr et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lisa, T" journalOrPublisher="Entomologia Basiliensia" pageId="42" pageNumber="85" refId="B74" refString="Lisa, T, 2002. Le Cicindele d'Italia (Coleoptera, Adephaga, Cicindelidae). Revue de l'Association Roussillonnaise d'Entomologie Supplement au Tome XI: 1-55." title="Le Cicindele d'Italia (Coleoptera, Adephaga, Cicindelidae). Revue de l'Association Roussillonnaise d'Entomologie Supplement au Tome XI: 1 - 55." year="2002">Lisa 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Vigna-Taglianti, A" editor="Minelli, A" journalOrPublisher="Calderini, Bologna" pageId="44" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 51" refId="B106" refString="Vigna-Taglianti, A, 1993. Coleoptera Archostemata, Adephaga 1 (Carabidae). In: Minelli, A, Ruffo, S, La, Posta S, Eds., Checklist delle specie della fauna italiana, 44. Calderini, Bologna: 1 - 51" title="Coleoptera Archostemata, Adephaga 1 (Carabidae)." volumeTitle="Checklist delle specie della fauna italiana, 44." year="1993">Vigna-Taglianti 1993</bibRefCitation>
), but is not listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pesarini, C" journalOrPublisher="Cornell University Press, Ithaca and London" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" refId="B92" refString="Pesarini, C, Monzini, V, 2010. Insetti della fauna Italiana - Coleotteri Carabidi I. Natura: Rivista di Scienze Naturali 100/2: 1-152." title="Insetti della fauna Italiana - Coleotteri Carabidi I. Natura: Rivista di Scienze Naturali 100 / 2: 1 - 152." year="2010">Pesarini and Monzini (2010)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="65" pageId="21" pageNumber="64">
In the southern Levant, both 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="64">
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1787" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calomera littoralis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="littoralis">Calomera littoralis</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Mandl" baseAuthorityYear="1934" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calomera winkleri" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="winkleri">Calomera winkleri</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName=", stat. rest." baseAuthorityName="J. R. Sahlberg" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calomera aulicoides" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aulicoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="64">Calomera aulicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur. They live in sympatry in the north of Israel (in the Hula Valley: see records for 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. littoralis subsp. winkleri" pageId="21" pageNumber="64" rank="subSpecies" species="littoralis" subSpecies="winkleri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="64">C. littoralis winkleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
published by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.578.7383" author="Matalin, AV" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" pagination="115 - 160" refId="B82" refString="Matalin, AV, Chikatunov, VI, 2016. The tiger beetles (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Cicindelinae) of Israel and adjacent lands. ZooKeys 578: 115 - 160, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.578.7383" title="The tiger beetles (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Cicindelinae) of Israel and adjacent lands." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.578.7383" volume="578" year="2016">Matalin and Chikatunov 2016</bibRefCitation>
, and own records of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. aulicoides" pageId="21" pageNumber="64" rank="species" species="aulicoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="64">C. aulicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Nahal Guvta (= Wadi al-Hashabi, in some maps indicated as Wadi Guyta; close to the Banias, CAL), while further southwest they are (at least) parapatric with a distance of about 20 km (Tamra - Eilabun) between populations. Although both taxa are flight-active, no intermediate forms are known (in contrast to the form of the copulatory pieces in the 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1787" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calomera littoralis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="littoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="64">Calomera littoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subspecies, see above). 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName=", stat. rest." baseAuthorityName="J. R. Sahlberg" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calomera aulicoides" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aulicoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="64">Calomera aulicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a clear and easily accessible character for differentiation from 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. littoralis" pageId="21" pageNumber="64" rank="species" species="littoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="64">C. littoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. While the latter one usually has three teeth on the inner side of the left mandible, 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. aulicoides" pageId="21" pageNumber="64" rank="species" species="aulicoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="64">C. aulicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has four of them (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 51" captionStartId="F27" captionText="Figure 51. Head of Calomera species in dorsal view: C. aphrodisia (left), C. aulicoides (right)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.734.21989.figure51" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/183632" pageId="21" pageNumber="64">51</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 52" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figure 52. Head of Calomera littoralis winkleri: with regular form of left mandible (left) and a small fourth tooth on the inner side of left mandible (arrow, right)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.734.21989.figure52" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/183633" pageId="21" pageNumber="64">52</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.578.7383" author="Matalin, AV" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" pagination="115 - 160" refId="B82" refString="Matalin, AV, Chikatunov, VI, 2016. The tiger beetles (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Cicindelinae) of Israel and adjacent lands. ZooKeys 578: 115 - 160, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.578.7383" title="The tiger beetles (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Cicindelinae) of Israel and adjacent lands." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.578.7383" volume="578" year="2016">Matalin and Chikatunov 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Sometimes specimens of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. littoralis subsp. winkleri" pageId="21" pageNumber="64" rank="subSpecies" species="littoralis" subSpecies="winkleri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="64">C. littoralis winkleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a small fourth 
<pageBreakToken pageId="22" pageNumber="65" start="start">tooth</pageBreakToken>
on the inner edge of the left mandible (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 52" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figure 52. Head of Calomera littoralis winkleri: with regular form of left mandible (left) and a small fourth tooth on the inner side of left mandible (arrow, right)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.734.21989.figure52" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/183633" pageId="22" pageNumber="65">52</figureCitation>
). However, these specimens do not represent hybrid populations as the copulatory piece of the median lobe of aedeagus does not show any intermediate characters. The lack of intermediate populations and the sympatric and parapatric distribution ranges in the southern Levant give evidence for the species status of both, 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. aulicoides" pageId="22" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="aulicoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="65">C. aulicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. littoralis" pageId="22" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="littoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="65">C. littoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="65">
It is possible that both taxa occur sympatrically in Jordan as well (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ma’in">Ma'in</normalizedToken>
Falls, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/21658005.2017.1400217" author="Nasir, WM" journalOrPublisher="Zoology and Ecology" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" pagination="269 - 291" refId="B85" refString="Nasir, WM, Katbeh-Bader, A, 2017. Annotated checklist of the ground beetles (Coleoptera: Carabidae) of Jordan. Zoology and Ecology 27: 269 - 291, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/21658005.2017.1400217" title="Annotated checklist of the ground beetles (Coleoptera: Carabidae) of Jordan." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/21658005.2017.1400217" volume="27" year="2017">Nasir and Katbeh-Bader 2017</bibRefCitation>
). We do not know any population of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. littoralis" pageId="22" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="littoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="65">C. littoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Jordan.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="65">
The external shapes of the median lobes of the aedeagi of both taxa do not differ strongly from each other (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 40" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 40. Median lobes of the aedeagus of species of the Calomera aulica group: a C. aulica b C. diania c C. aphrodisia." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.734.21989.figure40" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/183621" pageId="22" pageNumber="65">40</figureCitation>
), though the copulatory pieces are strongly differentiated (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 42. Copulatory pieces (arrows) of the median lobes of aedeagi of Calomera aulicoides (above) and C. littoralis winkleri (below)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.734.21989.figure42" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/183623" pageId="22" pageNumber="65">42</figureCitation>
). The sharp spines of the copulatory piece in these taxa may even act in a similar way to the spines of the endophallus in closely related 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carabus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Carabus</taxonomicName>
species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="(Ohomopterus)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Ohomopterus">Ohomopterus</taxonomicName>
, which seem to be an example of lock-and-key genitalia (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2411321" author="Sota, T" journalOrPublisher="Evolution" pageId="44" pageNumber="87" pagination="1507 - 1513" refId="B103" refString="Sota, T, Kubota, K, 1998. Genital lock-and-key as a selective agent against hybridization. Evolution 52: 1507 - 1513, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2411321" title="Genital lock-and-key as a selective agent against hybridization." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2411321" volume="52" year="1998">Sota and Kubota 1998</bibRefCitation>
). This is in contrast to most other animals, as in depth discussed by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10709-009-9358-y" author="Eberhard, WG" journalOrPublisher="Genetica" pageId="40" pageNumber="83" pagination="5 - 18" refId="B38" refString="Eberhard, WG, 2010. Evolution of genitalia: theories, evidence, and new directions. Genetica 138: 5 - 18, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s10709-009-9358-y" title="Evolution of genitalia: theories, evidence, and new directions." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10709-009-9358-y" volume="138" year="2010">Eberhard (2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.9780674330702" author="Eberhard, WG" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University Press, Cambridge" pageId="40" pageNumber="83" refId="B39" refString="Eberhard, WG, 1985. Sexual selection and animal genitalia. Harvard University Press, Cambridge, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.9780674330702" title="Sexual selection and animal genitalia." url="https://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.9780674330702" year="1985">1985</bibRefCitation>
). Caution is necessary in postulating lock-and-key-functions for the genitalia in tiger beetles as we lack empirical evidence.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="1223950" doi="10.3897/zookeys.734.21989.figure42" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/183623" pageId="22" pageNumber="65" start="Figure 42" startId="F18">
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="65">Figure 42.</emphasis>
Copulatory pieces (arrows) of the median lobes of aedeagi of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName=", stat. rest." baseAuthorityName="J. R. Sahlberg" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calomera aulicoides" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aulicoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="65">Calomera aulicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(above) and 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. littoralis subsp. winkleri" pageId="22" pageNumber="65" rank="subSpecies" species="littoralis" subSpecies="winkleri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="65">C. littoralis winkleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(below).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="1223954" doi="10.3897/zookeys.734.21989.figure43" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/183624" pageId="22" pageNumber="65" start="Figure 43" startId="F19">
